====Usage notes====
* This adjective is mostly restricted to attributive use; predicative uses such as in “My mother is stay-at-home” do exist, but are quite rare.
* In particular, this adjective is most commonly found in the expressions {{m|en||stay-at-home mother}}, {{m|en||father}}, {{m|en||mom}}, {{m|en||dad}}, {{m|en||motherhood}}, and so on, or else used in relation to the COVID-19 pandemic.

